In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2 cups for 4 servings), and a big
pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

Open and drain @Tofu{1}; press out excess water with #paper towels{}. Crumble tofu into pea-size
pieces over a #medium bowl{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{8%teaspoon} in large, preferably nonstick, pan over
medium-high heat. Add onion; season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, ~{3-4%minutes}.
Add @Red Cabbage and Carrot Mix{4%ounce}; continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until onions
are lightly browned and veggies are tender, ~{6-9%minutes}.

> TIP: If veggies begin to brown too quickly, add a few splashes of water and continue cooking
> until liquid has evaporated.

Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Heat 2 TBSP oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot, add crumbled tofu and spread
out in an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned on the bottom, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Stir, then cook until lightly browned all over, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat. Add veggies, @Soy Sauce{2%tablespoon}, @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1}, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%ounce}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Stir until tofu mixture is thoroughly coated.

Fluff rice with #fork{} and stir in lime zest to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Roughly chop @Peanuts{1%ounce}. Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with tofu and veggies, peanuts, a squeeze of lime juice, and
cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.